The paper deals with defending against adversarial attacks on deep neural networks using a preprocessing method based on the Saak transform. This involves computing spatial-spectral representations of input images, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the empirical results of their method, which involves training and testing neural networks (cs.LG) and the use of frequency analysis (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the use of filtering functions to process the images, which is a common technique in signal processing and machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the security aspect of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR).
